Lmod has detected the following error:

*** PLEASE READ THIS ENTIRE MESSAGE ***

---------------------------------------------------
IMPORTANT -=- IMPORTANT -=- IMPORTANT -=- IMPORTANT
---------------------------------------------------

You are seeing this message because you tried to load the 'bioinfo-tools'
module in Pelle.

The 'bioinfo-tools' module is not available on Pelle. It is not necessary
to load it to access bioinformatics software. On Pelle, bioinformatics
modules can be loaded directly. This is different from Rackham.

Many modules and module versions are already available on Pelle, but their
names may be capitalised differently and their versions are in a different
format. Use 'module avail modulename' or 'module spider modulename' to find
the new naming and available versions for your module.

For example, 'module avail samtools' shows (with a slightly different format):

----------------------- /sw/arch/eb/modules/all ------------------------
	SAMtools/0.1.20-GCC-13.3.0	SAMtools/1.19.2-GCC-13.3.0
	SAMtools/1.3.1-GCC-13.3.0	SAMtools/1.21-GCC-13.3.0
	SAMtools/1.12-GCC-13.3.0	SAMtools/1.22-GCC-13.3.0 (D)
	SAMtools/1.13-GCC-13.3.0

This tells you that the new spelling of the module is SAMtools and that there
are seven available versions. The '(D)' mark indicates that SAMtools/1.22 is
the default version loaded with 'module load SAMtools'. The default version
will change as new versions are installed. We recommend always specifying
module versions in your 'module load' commands.


LOADING MODULES
---------------

You can specify the module version by using just the version.

	module load SAMtools/1.21	(RECOMMENDED)

or using the full version and what is called the toolchain:

	module load SAMtools/1.21-GCC-13.3.0	(NOT RECOMMENDED)

We strongly recommend using the first method for specifying the version.
Toolchains (compilers, libraries, and associated utilities) are handled
hierarchically: some tools require a more simple toolchain than others, and it
is easier to ignore the toolchains. Also, the toolchain used to build a
particular module version may change as we make updates, but this should not
make any substantive difference to your use of the module. Toolchain names
include: GCCcore GCC gfbf gompi foss intel intelmpi


LET US KNOW
-----------

Contact UPPMAX support if

 - A module you need appears to be missing
 - You do not find your required version of a module
 - You notice weirdness with the module system
 - Or you have further questions about bioinformatics software on Pelle

Email us at

	support@uppmax.uu.se


